    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="236"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/147</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-31T22:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1917, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 1, 1918, 6.03
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8112. For War Trade Board from <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>:</p>
                <p>I cannot impress on you too strongly and [<hi rend="italic">the?</hi>]
                    desirability of cabling quickly answers to the following cables: 8085, December
                    28, 8 p.m.;<note n="1" xml:id="d236fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1107">p. 1107</ref>.</note>
                    8057, December 23, 11 a.m.;<note n="2" xml:id="d236fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1095">p. 1095</ref>.</note>
                    8041, December 21, 12 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">noon</hi>];<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d236fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1093">p. 1093</ref>.</note>
                    especially 8014, December 20, 9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>];<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d236fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1091">p. 1091</ref>.</note>
                    7952, December 13, 10 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>].<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d236fn5">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1085">p. 1085</ref>.</note> I
                    am unable usefully to assist at future Swedish conferences without instructions
                    from you on the points raised. The present favorably disposed Swedish Government
                    will, it is believed, face a difficult political situation on the 15th January
                    on the option of their Parliament unless they can make some favorable statement
                    toward fulfilling one of their pre-election promises of securing necessary
                    imports and we should not fail to take advantage of this situation which every
                    delay jeopardizes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
